modules.description: This module defines a set of visual styles for progress indicators, including UTF, ASCII, line, circle, braille, braille spin, and vertical formats. It is used to customize the appearance of progress bars and loading indicators in terminal interfaces. Concrete use cases include selecting a visual style for real-time progress tracking in command-line applications.

This module defines configuration options for progress bars, including style, total width, and prefix text. It works with records containing optional integer and string fields, alongside a separate style type. A concrete use case is customizing the visual appearance of a progress bar in a terminal interface.

This module implements in-place progress bars for terminal interfaces, supporting creation, incrementing, and customization of their behavior and appearance. It provides core operations to manage progress state, while child modules define visual styles like UTF or braille indicators and configuration options such as width and prefix text. You can, for example, display a UTF-style progress bar with a custom width and label, updating it dynamically as a loop progresses. Combining these features allows fine-grained control over progress visualization in command-line applications.

This module provides in-place terminal progress bars with support for dynamic updates, custom visual styles, and configurable display options like width and prefix text. The core functionality manages progress state, while child modules handle visual rendering using styles such as UTF or braille characters. You can create a labeled progress bar, update it within a loop, and customize its appearance to suit different terminal environments. For example, a UTF-style bar can be displayed with a custom width and label, updating in real-time as processing occurs.
